\b\i\f1\fs28\lang1033\langfe1033\cgrid\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {Using the JXTA Shell with Cougaar agents
\par }\pard\plain \ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0 \fs24\lang1033\langfe1033\cgrid\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {
\par The shell tool provided with the JXTA distribution (shell/s
hell/jxta.exe in the distribution) is very handy in analyzing Cougaar peer group functionality. Cougaar agents that establish themselves as JXTA peers using either the JXTAObjectSharePlugIn or the GroupFacilitatorPlugIn can be seen from the shell by issui
ng the \'93peers \endash r\'94 command (which broadcasts a request for online peers) and the \'93peers\'94 command (which lists the peers seen thus far). It may be required to flush the old peers listed in the cache using the \'93peers \endash f\'94
 command first of all.
\par 
\par Established peer groups can be listed by in the same way using \'93groups \endash f\'94, \'93groups \endash r\'94 and \'93groups\'94
 to flush, request and list peer groups respectively. This can be useful to determine if the GroupFacilitator successfully established the group.
\par 
\par To see if all the interested peers have joined a group, the shell peer can join the group as well using the \'93join \endash d\'94 command. After joining the group, the \'93peers \endash r\'94 and \'93peers\'94
 commands can be issued to list those peers that have successfully joined the peer group. 
\par 
\par Finally, it may be useful to see if the pipe advertisements have been established and published. This can be done using the \'93search \endash f\'94 , \'93search \endash r\'94 and \'93search\'94 commands to list current advertisements. 
\par 
