 to do things like advertising for peer interests or broadcasting peer capabilities. Developing a custom advertisement is straight forward and is pretty much a copy of the canonical advertisements provided by JXTA (
PeerAdvertisements, PeerGroupAdvertisements, PipeAdvertisements, etc.)
\par 
\par IMPORTANT NOTE:
\par In order for the JXTA infrastructure to recognize the newly created custom advertisement, the specification must be added to the config.properties file located in
\par net\\jxta\\impl\\config.properties. Normally, this file is read from the jxta.jar file in the class path, so using a modified version must come first in the class path, otherwise the default one in the jar file will
 be used and the custom advertisement will not be recognized.
\par 
